@subsection Informal introduction for beginners


A macro system allows us to give symbols in the S--expression of a
Scheme program the role of @dfn{syntactic keywords}; this means that a
subexpression is extracted from the program's S--expression and can be
processed by an appropriate function, called @dfn{transformer}, before
being put back.

